caption.body: “There is no better way to celebrate Pride Month at SFO than the completion of the first airport terminal in the world named for an LGBTQ leader that changed our city and our country,” said Mayor London Breed last month upon the opening of the final phase of Harvey Milk Terminal 1.  Have you been to the newly opened area of Harvey Milk Terminal 1? Featuring 15 new and returning works of art and two new Museum galleries, the new area also includes new ticket counters, security checkpoint, and a post-security connector to all terminals. The inaugural exhibitions in our new galleries celebrate San Francisco history. See “Flying on Display: Aviation at the Panama-Pacific International Exposition” located post-security and “Above SFO: The Aerial Photography of Marshall Moxom” located pre-security in Harvey Milk Terminal 1.  “Flying on Display: Aviation at the Panama-Pacific International Exposition” is online at: https://bit.ly/3zQVC0M   “Above SFO: The Aerial Photography of Marshall Moxom” is online at: https://bit.ly/4d5sOAh
